file: crates/ctx-cage/tests/bwrap_build.rs
behavior: Unit tests for the pure `bwrap` argv builder in `ctx_cage::bwrap`, asserting safety-cage semantics: writable workspace, masked secrets as regular files, unconditional network unshare, cleared env, explicit env re-injection, and RO toolchain/tool/rules/rundir binds.
edit_notes:
  - Exercises `build_bwrap_args`/`BwrapConfig` from ctx-cage::bwrap; any field renamed or removed there must be updated in `sample_config()`.
  - Depends on `CAGE_BIN`, `CAGE_RULES_PATH`, `CAGE_RUN_DIR` constants from the same module for expected cage-side paths.
  - Secret masks must bind a regular empty file (not `/dev/null`), since bind mounts carry `nodev` and would break readers like git; `workspace_is_bound_read_write_with_regular_file_secret_masks` enforces this by asserting `/dev/null` is absent from argv.
functions:
  - name: sample_config
    signature: fn sample_config() -> BwrapConfig
    purpose: Builds a representative BwrapConfig exercising every bind family for reuse across tests.
  - name: find
    signature: fn find(argv: &[OsString], needle: &str) -> Option<usize>
    purpose: Locates the index of a literal argv token.
  - name: assert_bind
    signature: fn assert_bind(argv: &[OsString], flag: &str, host: &str, cage: &str)
    purpose: Asserts a contiguous `flag host cage` triple exists in argv.
    notes: Panics via assert! if the triple is not found.
invariants:
  - build_bwrap_args must never emit `/dev/null` as a mask target.
  - `--new-session` is emitted only when BwrapConfig.new_session is true; `--unshare-net` is always present regardless.
external_deps: